Attalea funifera

   [3561.jpg]
    Authority   C. Martius ex Sprengel
      Family    Liliopsida:Arecidae:Arecales:Palmae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 3561

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION An evergreen tree (feather palm) reaching 12-15 m in
   height with up to 12 m long leaves. USES The fibre is strong, and hard
   and it does not absorb moisture easily, it is used for shrubbing
   brushes and stiff brooms. GROWING PERIOD Perennial. The seedlings grow
   down into the soil for 3-4 years, producing a stem below ground to a
   depth of 1-1.5 m, after a few more years a trunk may begin to form at
   ground level. COMMON NAMES Bahia piassava palm, Passabeira. FURTHER INF
   Bahia piassava palm is native to an area along the coast of Brazil in
   the state of Bahia. It can be found within the latitudinal range
   13-17Â°S. It is mainly found in dry forests.

   Sources
   SOURCES (A. funifera Mart.)
   Balick J 1986 pp 254-267 [TEMP, RAIN, TEXT, PH, DRA, FER, USE]
   Purseglove J 1972 pp 420 [USE]
   Kirby R 1963 pp 398-401 [TEXT, FER, USE]

